name: hell is other people
description:
it captures the vague moment of deciding whether or not to fully engage with another person.

sometimes we feel lonely and wander through deserted streets without a glimpse of light. in these moments we often make ourselves too dependent on other people’s opinions and define ourselves through them. when the desire and dependence becomes too high, it often ends in a hell of despair. 

learn to use other people's views and opinions in a way that moves you forward.
or as sartre said: hell is other people.
